Antenna I
in juvenile male of instar II (
Fig. 1S
) slightly broader than in female, with 9 terminal aesthetascs, with anlage of male seta about 1/4 length of antenna I. In adult (
Fig. 1Q
) it is broader than in female, with 12 terminal aesthetascs, two longest almost as long as antenna I itself, others about 2/3 length of antenna I. Male seta subterminal, about 1/3 length of antenna I.
